The default toolbar, below, comes preconfigured with shortcuts to tools that are
used most often. However if these do not suit your workflow, you can edit this
toolbar. For a refresher on how to work with the toolbar and customize it, 
please consult the [toolbar lesson][docwin-toolbarcustomize].

This reference describes the functions of all possible toolbar buttons.


![default toolbar](all-tbb-defaultset)


Toolbar Button Descriptions
----------------------------

| ![tidy options button](all-tbb-options)                | **Tidy Options Panel**: This toolbar button toggles the visibility of the **Tidy Options** panel.
| ![tidy feedback button](all-tbb-messages)              | **Feedback Panel**: This toolbar button toggles the visibility of the Feedback panel, that is, the panel that displays **Tidy Messages** and the **Browser Preview**.
| ![orient button](all-tbb-orient)                       | **Source Orientation**: This toolbar button toggles between viewing the **Source HTML** and **Tidy HTML** panels in a side-by-side and an over-and-under orientation.
| ![inline errors button](all-tbb-errorsinline)          | **Inline Errors**: This button toggles “red squiggles” in the **Source HTML**  that indicate the position of detected errors.
| ![invisible characters button](all-tbb-invisiblechars) | **Invisible Characters**: Pressing this button toggles the visibility of the invisible characters in the source panels.
| ![syntax highlighting button](all-tbb-syntaxcolor)     | **Syntax Highlighting**: You can toggle the use of syntax highlighting on and off with this toolbar button.
| ![editor gutter button](all-tbb-gutter)                | **Editor Gutter**: This toolbar button toggles the visibility of the editors’ line number gutter.
| ![preferences button](all-tbb-prefs)                   | **Preferences**: This toolbar button opens <%= pne %>’s Preferences window.
| ![tutorial button](all-tbb-tutorialb)                  | **Quick Tutorial**: This toolbar button starts the **Quick Tutorial**.
| ![space button](all-tbb-space)                         | **Space**: This toolbar item is a space that you can insert into the toolbar to help you organize it during customization.
| ![flexible space button](all-tbb-flexspace)            | **Flexible Space**: This toolbar item is a space that you can insert into the  toolbar to help you organize it during customization.
| ![print button](all-tbb-print)                         | **Print**: This toolbar button will open the **Print** dialog for the document.
| ![help button](all-tbb-help)                           | **Help**: This toolbar button opens the Help file for <%= pne %>.
